President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Anthony F. Godfrey as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Serbia. Godfrey is a career member of the U.S. Navy and the Foreign Service, currently serving as Deputy Chief of Mission at the U.S. Embassy in Moscow, Russia. He has previously held positions in the U.S. Department of State, including Director of the Office of Iraq Affairs and Minister-Counselor for Political Affairs at the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad.

Additionally, Leslie Meredith Tsou has been nominated as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Sultanate of Oman. Tsou is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and is currently Deputy Chief of Mission at the U.S. Mission in Israel, and the first Deputy Chief of Mission of the U.S. Embassy in Jerusalem. She has held various positions at the Department of State, including Senior Advisor on Iran and Director of the Office of Iranian Affairs.

President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint John DeStefano as a Member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, expiring in September 2021.